# Tailwind CSS

## Setup

- **Tailwind v4** via `@tailwindcss/vite` in `astro.config.mjs` → `vite.plugins`
- Entry: `@import "tailwindcss"` in `src/styles/global.css`
- Theme tokens: `@theme { }` block in `global.css` (brand colours, fonts)
- Brand CSS variables: `src/styles/tokens.css` (for inline styles & non-utility use)
- Typography: `@plugin '@tailwindcss/typography'` in `global.css`

Do **not** use `@astrojs/tailwind` — deprecated; incompatible with Tailwind v4.

## When to use what

| Use | For |
|---|---|
| Tailwind classes | Layout, spacing, flex/grid, responsive, typography weight |
| `text-ab-green`, `bg-rich-black` | Brand colours from `@theme` |
| Inline `style=` | `clamp()` typography, gradients, filters, one-off brand values |
| CSS variables | Global tokens in `tokens.css` |

## Brand colour classes

```
ab-green   #006A52    ab-gold    #D6A02A
ab-beige   #D3BC8D    ab-neon    #00FF1F (digital only)
rich-black #0A0A09    charcoal   #0A0A09
```

## Common patterns

```html
<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
<div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20 items-center">
```

## Astro vs React

- `.astro` files: `class="..."`
- React islands: `className="..."`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge conditional classes in TSX

## Adding theme tokens

Extend `@theme` in `global.css` — use `--color-*` for colours, `--font-*` for fonts:

```css
@theme {
  --color-ab-green: #006a52;
}
```
